= SDL_GetTextureColorMod =
Use this function to get the additional color value used in render copy operations.


== Syntax ==
```c++
int SDL_GetTextureColorMod(SDL_TextureID textureID,
                           Uint8*        r,
                           Uint8*        g,
                           Uint8*        b)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''textureID'''
|the texture to query
|-
|'''r'''
|a pointer filled in with the source red color value
|-
|'''g'''
|a pointer filled in with the source green color value
|-
|'''b'''
|a pointer filled in with the source blue color value
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns 0 on success or -1 if the texture is not valid; call [[SDL_GetError]]() for more information.

